Arbroath appoint Todd Lumsden as full-time manager
Todd Lumsden has been appointed full-time manager of Arbroath after signing a two-year deal.Lumsden was Allan Moore's assistant and has been caretaker boss sinceMoore was sacked less than a year into the job.He was previously player-manager of Albion Rovers during the 2012/13 season, but left after they were relegated from the second division.Arbroath could yet secure promotion from Scottish League Two after making the play-offs last weekend.